 against branch origin/trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14357351" author="becket_qin" created="Wed, 11 Mar 2015 18:30:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just submitted another small fix patch.&lt;br/&gt;
I just realized that I still need to add unacked offset into unacked offsets list before calling producer.send(), because the callback can also be fired in producer.send().&lt;br/&gt;
The reason I added the unacked offset after calling producer.send() was that I&apos;m worrying that if something wrong in producer.send() occurs, the offset would never be removed, but since we exiting on any exception in producer thread, it might not cause further problem as the entire mirror maker will exit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
